		<div id="unique-entry-id-251" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Halloween</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 27 October 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-side-tracked.php">Side Tracked</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>I am dressing as Ma Kettle for Halloween.  I hope you all enjoy halloween to and get the chance to dress up too.<br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-250" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Vampire films</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 26 October 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-vampires.php">Vampires</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.alexrider.com/News/Anthony-Horowitz-presents-Crocodile-Tears" rel="external" title="http://www.alexrider.com/News/Anthony-Horowitz-presents-Crocodile-Tears"><img class="imageStyle" alt="books" src="books.jpg" width="42" height="40" /></a></div>Teen books be turned into film are popular at the moment.  Cirque Du Freak: The Vampire's Assistant is out at the cinema and for all you Twilight fans New Moon comes out on 20th November (UK, US and Canada)<br />See <a href="http://www.newmoonthemovie.com/" rel="external" title="http://www.newmoonthemovie.com/">www.newmoonthemovie.com</a> to check if it is same for your country.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-249" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Prince Philip School</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 18 October 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-side-tracked.php">Side Tracked</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></div>I have mentioned before that my son's school's nickname and logo is the 'pirates'.  So for talk like a pirate day the whole school even teachers (and the attached pre-school) dressed up as pirates.  It was really worth seeing and they did take a photo where they were being pirates (not the usual look at the camera and smile).  Sadly it looks as if will not be online.<br /><br />Also on the subject of the school, I would like to congratulate them, as next week the are celebrating their fiftieth birthday.  They are even in possession of a birthday letter from Prince Philip at Buckingham Palace.  Way to go guys keep up enjoying yourselves.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-248" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Crocodile Tears</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 10 October 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.alexrider.com/News/Anthony-Horowitz-presents-Crocodile-Tears" rel="external" title="http://www.alexrider.com/News/Anthony-Horowitz-presents-Crocodile-Tears"><img class="imageStyle" alt="books" src="books.jpg" width="42" height="40" /></a></div>Alex Rider by Anthony Horowitz may not be a Vampirate book but it is one of the books I have been looking out for.  It is coming out on 12th November in the UK and I have already pre-ordered my copy (from Red House with it's exclusive letter from Anthony Horowitz) to be sent to my Mother-in-Law.  Incase I cannot find it in this part of the world or like Black Heart the hard back copy has not got neat edges.<br /><br />For everyone in the UK Anthony Horowitz is doing a bit of a tour.  If you are interested please see <a href="http://www.alexrider.com/News/Anthony-Horowitz-presents-Crocodile-Tears" rel="external" title="http://www.alexrider.com/News/Anthony-Horowitz-presents-Crocodile-Tears">www.alexrider.com/News/Anthony-Horowitz-presents-Crocodile-Tears</a><br /></div></div>
